==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gulch
<hw>Gulch</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Act of
gulching or gulping.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A glutton.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>B.
Jonson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A ravine, or part of the deep bed of a torrent when
dry; a gully.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gulch</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Gulch
<hw>Gulch</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>gulchen</ets>; cf. dial.
Sw. <ets>g⟦oum⟧lka</ets> to <ets>gulch</ets>, D. <ets>gulzig</ets>
greedy, or E. <ets>gulp</ets>.]</ety> <def>To swallow greedily; to gulp
down.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Guld</ent>⟦br⟧
